TMK Board Recommends First-Half Dividend of 93 Kopeks a Share

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-09-26T07:18:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/tmk-board-recommends-first-half-dividend-of-93-kopeks-a-share.html
OAO TMK,  Russia ’s largest producer
of steel pipes for the oil and gas industry, may pay a first-
half dividend of 93 kopeks a share, for payout of 872 million
rubles ($27 million).  Shareholders will vote on the board’s recommendation at a
Nov. 7 meeting, the Russian pipemaker said today in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Torrey Clark at 
 tclark8@bloomberg.net  